Johannesburg A 32-year-old man who robbed a woman of her cellphone in Durban earlier this year has been sentenced to 10 years imprisonment.Sandile Ndlovu was convicted and sentenced for robbery by the Durban Regional Court.KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said that on 20 May, at about 15:20, a 22-year-old victim was walking along Smith street in Durban when she was approached by the accused who robbed her of her cellphone. A case of robbery was opened at Durban Central Police station for further investigation.Zwane said the accused was apprehended and he made several court appearances until he was convicted and sentenced . African News Agency